			</contentSection><contentSection id="5">
				<title>
					Livin' Creature Style
				</title>
				<navigationLabel>
					Livin' Praying Mantis Style!
				</navigationLabel>
				<contentItems>
					<contentItem id="126">
						<title>
							
						</title>
						<text>
							Many species of mantises are ambush predators.  They will sit very still waiting for prey to come close before shooting out their raptorial arms and catching it. Before the prey has a chance to escape, they will start their dinner! Other species, like Litugursa krattorum, chase down their prey with incredible speed!
						</text>
